hesml.taxonomy

Interface IVertexList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<IVertex>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VertexList

    public interface IVertexList
extends java.lang.Iterable<IVertex>
    This interface represents an abstract ordered collection of taxonomy vertexes as defined in the HESML paper below. Lastra-Díaz, J. J., and García-Serrano, A. (2016). HESML: a scalable ontology-based semantic similarity measures library with a set of reproducible experiments and a replication dataset. Submitted for publication to the Information Systems Journal.
    Author:
    Juan Lastra-Díaz

      This function computes the difference set as regards the input set.

      This function computes element count in the difference set.
      int getGreatestDepthMax()
      This function returns the greatest depth value among all the vertexes contained in the list, where the depth is defined as the length of the longest ascending path from any vertex to the root, so called DepthMax in HESML library.
      int getGreatestDepthMin()
      This function returns the greatest depth value among all the vertexes contained in the list, where the depth is defined as the length of the shortest ascending path from any vertex to the root, so called DepthMin in HESML library.

      This function returns the greatest depth value in base 1.

      • clear

        void clear()
    throws java.lang.Exception
        This function removes all the vertexes in the list, releasing the memory space. This function only can be invoked for non-locked lists as all the vertex list computed on-the-fly. The only locked list is the global vertexes list of the taxonomy.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Unexpected error
